UPDATE YOUR APPLICATION WITHOUT DOWN TIME

First get all deployments
$ kubectl get deployment

Choose Which deployment application you want to update
$ kubectl set image deployment/<deployment_name> <deployment_name>=<latest image src>

Check status of your updated application
$ kubectl rollout status deployment/<deployment_name>

Check History of Your Updated application
$ kubectl rollout history deployment/<deployment_name>

If you want to Undo your previous application
$ kubectl rollout undo deployment/<deployment_name>

check description of your deployment
$ kubectl describe deployment <deployment_name>

